steps.instruction:
- Preheat oven to 350F
- Cut breasts in half
- Sprinkle the breast halves with salt and pepper to taste
- Place them in a lightly greased 9x13 inch baking dish
- In a small bowl combine honey, mustard, basil, paprika and parsley
- Mix well
- Pour *half* the mix onto the chicken, brush to cover
- Bake in oven for 30 minutes
- Turn the pieces over and brush with the remaining half of the mixture
- Bake for an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until the chicken is no longer pink 
- Let it cool for 10 minutes
